Fribourg.title: Fribourg
Fribourg.byline: Fribourg is a city in Switzerland that is also the canton's capital and economic centre.

Friedrichshafen.title: Friedrichshafen
Friedrichshafen.byline: Friedrichshafen  is a city at the northeastern corner of Lake Constance (Bodensee), near the lake's widest point in the German federal-state of Baden-Württemberg.

Friesland.title: Friesland
Friesland.byline: It is known for its unique language and culture.

Frigiliana.title: Frigiliana
Frigiliana.byline: Frigiliana is a mountain town in Andalucia, Spain.

Frinton-on-Sea.title: Frinton-on-Sea
Frinton-on-Sea.byline: Frinton-on-Sea is a small seaside town in the Tendring district of Essex.

Frisian Lakes.title: Frisian Lakes
Frisian Lakes.byline: While the Frisian Lakes (Dutch: Friese meren, West Frisian: Fryske marren) are not well known among foreigners, the locals flock to this tourist area in great numbers.

Fritch.title: Fritch
Fritch.byline: Fritch is a city in the High Plains region of Texas.

Friuli-Venezia Giulia.title: Friuli-Venezia Giulia
Friuli-Venezia Giulia.byline: Friuli-Venezia Giulia is an autonomous region of Italy, the country's most northeasterly region, on the borders with Austria and Slovenia.

Friedberg (Hesse).title: Friedberg (Hesse)
Friedberg (Hesse).byline: Friedberg is a charming medieval town dating to the 12th or 13th century in North Hesse.
